text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus pentacycla is an uncommon Asian species of tree in the beech family. It has been found only in the Province of Yunnan in southwestern China.Quercus pentacycla is a tree up to 15 meters tall. Twigs are grayish brown. Leaves can be as much as 14 cm long.
